WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Steph, obviously with Dylan out, you're handling the ball more than ever.

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:10.000
Are there other factors that go into the turnovers?

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:15.000
Is there anything you guys need to tighten up just all the way around offensively?

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:20.000
I think it's more personal.

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
On my end, just really speeding myself up.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.000
Not allowing our screeners to get hit.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:32.000
It's putting me in a position where I have to play fast

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
or my screener might get offensive foul.

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
I put us at a disadvantage to start the game with those.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:46.000
Some of it comes with fatigue, but at this point of the season it's really no excuse.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:51.000
Steph, I know you guys don't use injuries as excuses for anything that happens,

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:56.000
but what are the differences between you guys have had experience playing without your key guys,

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
what's the difference between going into a game knowing that they're going to be out

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
versus losing a player midway through a game like Dylan tonight?

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
It's tough.

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:14.000
Regardless, I think the five guys on the court are pretty much connected at all times.

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:20.000
Obviously we want all of our guys to be healthy and be on the court.

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:27.000
Just to see if they might go out mid-game gives you a little bit more motivation to do it for them.

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:33.000
But after coming into the game, we had the same mindset with Fox out.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:42.000
Obviously one person can't make up for what Fox or somebody else can't make up for what no deal brings for us.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:45.000
Just trying to do it as a team.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:49.000
Steph, Wallace was pressing you against the backcourt line a ton.

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:54.000
Have you had to deal with that level of ball pressure in the NBA at this point?

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:59.000
How did you guys try to get out of those situations where you know you can't be trapped against those lines

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:02.000
because there's an extra defender out there?

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:07.000
It's not the first time we've been pressured.

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:11.000
We've been playing basketball for a long time.

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:15.000
We get pressured as guards all the time.

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:20.000
It was something that we talked about and went over with our coaches.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:23.000
I mean, you've got to be better and cleaner with it.

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:25.000
Fox has been mentoring you all season.

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:29.000
What was his message to you tonight when he realized he wasn't going to go

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:31.000
and you had those 11 turnovers last game?

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:35.000
How do you feel like you lived up to what you were hoping to do tonight

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:37.000
and what could you do better?

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:42.000
Yeah, I mean, the big thing is just playing off two feet,

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:45.000
not getting sped up.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:49.000
I mean, obviously, I did do a great job of that.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:02:54.000
But yeah, just trying to keep my teammates involved,

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:58.000
trying not to do too much on the offensive end,

00:02:58.000 --> 00:03:01.000
trying to make the simple play as much as I can.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:06.000
I mean, yeah, even after having all those turnovers,

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.000
we still gave ourselves a chance to win.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
So, I mean, leaving here with that is definitely a plus.

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
Steph, how much does your individual mentality change

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:19.000
when both Dylan and the Aaron are out?

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:24.000
Does it require a different approach from you overall?

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:29.000
I don't know if I've played a game with both of them out

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:32.000
earlier in the year. I don't think so.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:34.000
I mean, yes. I mean, it's tough.

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:37.000
I mean, having another ball handler on the court

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:41.000
at all times is definitely a luxury.

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:44.000
I think, you know, Jay Mac played big minutes today

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:49.000
when he came in, helped me out, helped us out a ton.

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:51.000
So, I mean, yeah, it's tough.

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:55.000
But I think just, you know, with all of our energy,

00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:58.000
mainly focused on the defensive end,

00:03:58.000 --> 00:04:00.000
I just think, well, me personally,

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:03.000
I just have to take my time a lot more on the offensive end

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:06.000
and try and make, you know, the simple read as much as I can.

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:10.000
Steph, Coach said you were a warrior out there tonight.

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:13.000
How do you balance that attack mindset

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:18.000
and always attacking with the patience and that part of it?

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:24.000
Yeah, I think the way that they guard,

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:27.000
they do a good job of trying to bait you

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:29.000
into playing one-on-one.

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:33.000
And a lot of the times you can probably go create your own shot,

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:36.000
but I think for the team and for the way that we play,

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:38.000
we don't want to play that way.

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:41.000
So, I mean, trying to balance, you know, when to be aggressive

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:44.000
versus, you know, keeping my teammates involved

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:46.000
and trying to make the right pass,

00:04:46.000 --> 00:04:48.000
make sure everybody's in rhythm.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:50.000
So, I mean, yeah, it's tough,

00:04:50.000 --> 00:04:52.000
but I mean, we've seen them multiple times

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:54.000
and it's kind of been the same theme with them.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:58.000
So, I mean, yeah, I mean, that's the luxury of, you know,

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:00.000
playing in a series, you know, you lose a game

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:02.000
and you get to go back and look at it

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:04.000
and see what you did wrong.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:09.000
Steph, you guys preached about short-term memory all season long.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:13.000
How, you guys are going back to San Antonio on Friday.

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:18.000
How are you going to prepare yourself for San Antonio

00:05:18.000 --> 00:05:22.000
and mentally get back to where you need to get to

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:25.000
before your goal that you have in the season?

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:28.000
I mean, we're probably most comfortable

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:31.000
playing in front of our fans.

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:34.000
So, I mean, I don't think we'll have any problem doing that,

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:39.000
but I mean, mentally, I think we're all in a good headspace.

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:42.000
We came here, you know, won a game on the road

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:44.000
and they're a good team and they responded.

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:46.000
So, you know, now we have a chance

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:48.000
to play in front of our fans.

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:51.000
So, I mean, I think we'll erase this game pretty quick.

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:54.000
I don't want to watch it and, you know, go through it

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:57.000
and scout it, but I mean, yeah, I mean,

00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:59.000
looking forward to next game, it's in two days.

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:03.000
So, I mean, we've done a good job of having short-term memory

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:04.000
all season.

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:06.000
So, I don't see what to change.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:09.000
Steph, what would you say was the biggest challenge

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:12.000
with containing O.K.C.'s pace tonight?

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:15.000
I think it started probably with,

00:06:15.000 --> 00:06:19.000
probably a lot with my turnovers, honestly.

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:21.000
Them being able to get out and transition

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:24.000
and, you know, get a rhythm that early.

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:26.000
I think they, I don't know how many points they had

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:30.000
in transition in the first half, probably, like, 15, 16.

00:06:30.000 --> 00:06:33.000
So, and it was like a eight-point game.

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:37.000
So, I mean, yeah, just trying to take care of the ball,

00:06:37.000 --> 00:06:38.000
you know, the offensive end

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:41.000
and forcing the play against our half-court defense.

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:42.000
I feel like for the most part,

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:44.000
we've been pretty solid in our half-court defense.

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
So, just not allowing our offense to hurt our defense.

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:50.000
Steph, I want to take you back to the second quarter.

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:52.000
You have a pretty big dunk that in normal games

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:54.000
would change momentum swings,

00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.000
yet it swings the momentum the other way,

00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:58.000
like immediately in the eight quarters

00:06:58.000 --> 00:07:00.000
that you guys have played because they over time

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:03.000
didn't seem like anybody can grab the momentum.

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:06.000
Can you just talk about the mental exhaustion

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:07.000
of getting back and forth

00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:09.000
and just not being able to grab the momentum

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:12.000
and just going back and forth in that tug-of-war?

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:17.000
Yeah, I think it's a game of runs.

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:20.000
And I think with high-level teams like that,

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:22.000
there's a lot of talent on the floor

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:25.000
and, you know, typically that comes with big plays.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:29.000
But I just think with all the talent that is on the floor,

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:31.000
I feel like everybody's, you know,

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:32.000
seen the play like that before.

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:35.000
So, you know, you kind of wash it pretty quick

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:37.000
and get back to, you know, playing basketball.

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:40.000
So, I think they did a good job of that,

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:41.000
especially in that quarter.

00:07:41.000 --> 00:07:44.000
So, I mean, I think we just got to be better.

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:46.000
Not sure if you've been asked yet about Dylan Harper

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:48.000
getting all rookie at first team,

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:49.000
but I wanted to ask about the character

00:07:49.000 --> 00:07:51.000
that he's brought to this first team this year.

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:53.000
Yeah.

00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:57.000
Dylan's really good.

00:07:57.000 --> 00:07:59.000
I think he's going to be a great player in this league

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:01.000
for a long time.

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:04.000
I mean, he's super humble and super selfless

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:06.000
with, you know, how good he is.

00:08:06.000 --> 00:08:09.000
So, you know, I'm happy that he got that award.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:11.000
He was very deserving of it.

00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:14.000
So, I mean, you'll see a lot of accolades

00:08:14.000 --> 00:08:18.000
from him for a long time.

